                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="12996440" author="rickhall" created="Fri, 18 Feb 2011 14:56:24 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Yeah, that sounds like a bug, but I wouldn&apos;t worry about it unless you need a fix right now, since I will be committing some major resolver changes probably next week that totally re-write fragment handling.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12996450" author="gnt" created="Fri, 18 Feb 2011 15:22:22 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I think the problem is really limited to PackageAdmin.  Maybe PackageAdmin should just return an empty host list is the fragment isn&apos;t resolved and should prune the list of fragments attached to those that are actually resolved ?  Not sure the resolution process is involved here.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12996456" author="rickhall" created="Fri, 18 Feb 2011 15:33:35 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;In trunk, I agree, the resolution process isn&apos;t involved. But the new version of the resolver doesn&apos;t pre-attach fragments, so this issue might not even exist once it is committed.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
